<div id="t1b">
<div class="topic"><div class="tnum">1b</div><div><div class="ttitle">Data Science Life Cycle</div><div class="tsub">Stages · Diagram · Common Misconceptions</div></div><span class="badge by">Must Read — Core Diagram</span></div>
<div class="pyq">📋 Asked in: June'24 ("stages of data science life cycle with diagram", 8 marks) — likely to repeat as it's a core Unit 1 diagram</div>
<div class="sec">💡 Understand It Simply</div>
<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What it actually means</div><p>Every data science project follows roughly the same journey — from "what's the business question?" to "here's the working model deployed." This life cycle is the roadmap every data scientist follows, regardless of the specific problem.</p></div>
<div class="sec">🔑 Keywords to Memorise</div>
<div class="keywords"><div class="kl">These words MUST appear in your answer</div>
<div class="kw-grid"><span class="kw">Requirements Analysis</span><span class="kw">Data Collection and Preparation</span><span class="kw">Descriptive Data Analysis</span><span class="kw">Modelling and Testing</span><span class="kw">Model Deployment and Refinement</span><span class="kw">Iterative process</span><span class="kw">Correlation ≠ Causation</span><span class="kw">Simpson's Paradox</span></div></div>
<div class="sec">✍ 8/10 Mark Answer</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Data Science Life Cycle with Diagram + Misconceptions</span><span class="marks10">8-10 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>The Data Science Life Cycle is the <span class="kh">iterative process</span> followed in every data science project, moving through five connected stages:</p>
