<p>This is an <span class="kh">iterative process</span> — insights from later stages often send you back to earlier stages for refinement, not a strict one-way line.</p>
<p><strong>Common Misconceptions in Data Analysis:</strong> <span class="kh">Correlation ≠ Causation</span> — two variables moving together doesn't mean one causes the other (e.g., attendance and marks are both caused by student motivation, not each other). <span class="kh">Simpson's Paradox</span> — a trend in combined data can reverse when split into subgroups, due to uneven group sizes distorting the overall picture.</p>
