<p>MapReduce is a programming framework processing massive datasets in <span class="kh">parallel processing</span> across many computers, using <span class="kh">key-value pairs</span> throughout.</p>
<p><strong>Word Count Example — Input: "data is big data"</strong></p>
<div class="formula">MAP PHASE (each word → 1):
  &lt;data,1&gt; &lt;is,1&gt; &lt;big,1&gt; &lt;data,1&gt;

SHUFFLE &amp; SORT (group by key):
  &lt;data,[1,1]&gt; &lt;big,[1]&gt; &lt;is,[1]&gt;

REDUCE PHASE (sum values):
  &lt;data,2&gt; &lt;big,1&gt; &lt;is,1&gt;

PSEUDO-CODE:
function MAP(key, value):
    for each word w in value:
