<div id="t14">
<div class="topic"><div class="tnum">13</div><div><div class="ttitle">Bloom Filter</div><div class="tsub">Working · Need · Illustrative Example</div></div><span class="badge by">2-3 Papers</span></div>
<div class="pyq">📋 Asked in: Dec'24, Dec'25 (10 marks) — recently a dedicated 10-mark question</div>
<div class="sec">💡 Understand It Simply</div>
<div class="understand"><div class="ul">What it actually means</div><p>A web crawler has visited millions of URLs. For every new URL it must ask "have I seen this before?" Storing millions of URLs for exact checking is too slow and memory-heavy. A Bloom Filter answers this fast and memory-efficiently, but occasionally gives a false "yes" (never a false "no").</p></div>
<div class="sec">🔑 Keywords to Memorise</div>
<div class="keywords"><div class="kl">These words MUST appear in your answer</div>
<div class="kw-grid"><span class="kw">Bit array</span><span class="kw">Multiple hash functions</span><span class="kw">Space-efficient</span><span class="kw">Probabilistic membership test</span><span class="kw">False positives possible</span><span class="kw">False negatives impossible</span></div></div>

<div class="sec">✍ 5-Mark Answer — Core</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Bloom Filter — Quick Version</span><span class="marks5">5 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>A Bloom Filter is a <span class="kh">space-efficient</span> structure testing set membership via a <span class="kh">probabilistic membership test</span>, using a <span class="kh">bit array</span> and <span class="kh">multiple hash functions</span>.</p>
<p>Adding an item sets k bit positions to 1. Checking: if ALL positions are 1, "probably present"; if ANY is 0, "definitely absent." <span class="kh">False positives possible</span>, <span class="kh">false negatives impossible</span>.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="sec">✍ 10-Mark Answer — With Worked Example</div>
<div class="ans-card"><div class="ans-head"><span>Bloom Filter — Need, Working, and Example</span><span class="marks10">10 Marks</span></div>
<div class="ans-body">
<p>A Bloom Filter is a <span class="kh">space-efficient</span> data structure testing membership using a <span class="kh">probabilistic membership test</span> instead of storing the full set.</p>
<p><strong>Need:</strong> Storing millions of URLs in memory for exact lookup is impossible at scale. Bloom Filters compress this into a tiny <span class="kh">bit array</span> while preserving fast lookup.</p>
<p><strong>Working:</strong> Create a bit array of n bits, all 0. Use k <span class="kh">multiple hash functions</span> — adding an item sets those k positions to 1. Checking: ALL positions 1 → "probably present"; ANY position 0 → "definitely absent."</p>
<p><strong>Example:</strong> 10-bit array, 2 hash functions. Add "apple" → sets bits 2,5. Add "mango" → sets bits 5,8. Check "banana" → hashes to bits 2,8 — both already 1 from other items → says "probably present" though never added. This is a <span class="kh">false positive</span>.</p>
<p><strong>Key properties:</strong> <span class="kh">False positives possible</span>, <span class="kh">false negatives impossible</span> — it never misses an actual member, only occasionally over-reports.</p>
</div></div>
</div>
